<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1925-02-10T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1925-02-10T15:00:00-05:00" n="337" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d337">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">875.6363/160: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Albania</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Grant-Smith</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1925-02-10T15:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">February 10,
                                        1925—3 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>7. The Department has information that Mr. Sheffield<note n="10" xml:id="d337fn10">E. S. Sheffield, representative of the Standard
                                Oil Co. of New York.</note> is shortly to leave the United States
                            and will proceed at once to Tirana, where he should arrive about
                            February 28th.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>